originalText.text: I just came out of this store located at 333 7TH AVE, NEW YORK, NY 10001. I had an appointment at 5.30pm for 2 vaccines. The pharmacy personnel was extremely slow, rude and unmotivated. The security person was attacked, thrown things at by an individual who was stealing. I tried to interfere and help the security guard who probably can do nothing except risking his life. Meanwhile, the pharmacist continued being rude and incompetent whereas the doctor being 45mns late and obviously not caring about it, I left the store without having had my vaccines. Thank you so much for the wonderful customer experience. Never again.

originalText.text: I had an incredibly disappointing experience at this Pharmacy. I went in with a prescription that needed to be filled urgently, but the staff was extremely unhelpful. When I explained my situation, they told me they were too busy to take my prescription and that I should come back later. I understand that they might have been busy, but their dismissive and rude attitude was completely unwarranted. Instead of trying to help me, they made me feel like an inconvenience. I was shocked by their lack of empathy and customer service skills. As a result, I will never be returning to this Pharmacy, and I strongly advise others to avoid it as well.

originalText.text:
I've read the horrible reviews this place has so I was a bit anxious to go get my flu shot there the other day.  I was running a little behind schedule and called to see if that would make a difference and the person on the phone was very friendly. I was still nervous about the actual in-store experience though.

When I got there, I found things to be different from the online reviews for me. I was greeted by a two person team who were very friendly.

By the pharmacy, the person behind the counter was very nice and seemed especially grateful that I filled out my forms online before the appointment.  I had to wait a little while before the vaccination, but while waiting, I saw other people being helped by workers who seemed accommodating and helpful. Since I gave my insurance info, I was offered four free Binax covid tests if I wanted them.  The flu shot itself was fast and painless although the bandaid had some difficulty staying on after a little while.  But I didn't really need it at that point anyway.

The only reason I gave four stars instead of five was because I noticed the shelves weren't as stocked as they could have been.  It was the middle of the afternoon and some areas were fairly bare.

I'm not saying that the other reviews aren't valid, but my experience yesterday was a pleasant one.
